in the implementation of the data-centre integration, File inventory & reversibility

  2 NEW files (full removal = rm):
  1. tools/teable_knowledge_tool.py
  2. skills/knowledge/SKILL.md (also creates the skills/knowledge/ directory)

  2 MODIFIED files (revert via git checkout):
  3. toolsets.py — two edits: 6 names appended to _HERMES_CORE_TOOLS (around line 65) + one "knowledge" entry in the TOOLSETS dict (around line 255)
  4. tools/skill_usage.py — one edit: add "knowledge" to the PROTECTED_BUILTIN_SKILLS set (line 66)

  Zero files outside the repo are modified by the code change itself.

  Removal procedure (clean uninstall)

  # Inside repo
  rm tools/teable_knowledge_tool.py
  rm -rf skills/knowledge/
  git checkout -- toolsets.py tools/skill_usage.py

  That's it. All four touch-points are reverted, and the auto-discovery loop at tools/registry.py:57 will no longer find the tool file (so the tools vanish from the schema on next CLI start). The skill index rebuilder at
  agent/prompt_builder.py:1118 will no longer find skills/knowledge/SKILL.md (so the skill vanishes from the system prompt).

  User-side state that may linger

  These are NOT created by the code change — they're side-effects of running it. All optional to clean:

