  No external side effects: no Teable schema changes (the API is read/write to records only), no migrations, no config-file writes by the agent, no DB writes outside Teable, no network calls during install.

  Risk profile: the integration is purely additive and gated behind TEABLE_TOKEN. If you delete just the tool file and leave the rest, the tools fail to register but nothing else breaks (toolset entry just references missing
  tool names, which the registry silently skips). So even a partial cleanup is safe.